20/07/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Carla del Ponte, the chief prosecutor for the UN war crimes tribunal, arrived Friday (18 July) on an official visit. She expressed dissatisfaction with the level of co-operation shown by Republika Srpska (RS), especially in efforts to detain war crimes suspects. She demanded concrete action, saying she expects results. During his meeting with del Ponte, RS President Dragan Cavic said that authorities are committed to improving efforts. RS Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic said several names were discussed, but he did not elaborate. (HINA, TV Hayat, ATV - 18/07/03)
